The paper discusses the creation of a global knowledge system using a new philosophy and infrastructure of a global distributed semantic network. This involves the construction of a space-time database environment for binding documents to permanent entities, leading to new knowledge representation and retrieval techniques. This work involves aspects of database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), deep learning (cs.DL), and machine learning (cs.LG).
